Start your week with the final return of a Golden Globe-winning series about money, death, love, murder and dreams coming true; a reality competition about a group of castaways who inhabit an island where they are forced to compete against each other in a series of challenges; and a marriage coaching show that will see couples go on a journey of learning how to build a healthy and loving marriage. The Golden Globe-winning Netflix show, The Kominsky Method is set for another outing. Sandy Kominsky has to navigate what ageing looks like without his longtime friend Norman Newlander by his side in the final season. Life only becomes more complicated with the arrival of Sandy’s ex-wife Roz Volander. The pair’s famously volatile relationship is further inflamed when she comes to L.A. to spend time with their daughter Mindy and her boyfriend Martin. This season of ‘The Kominsky Method’ deals with money, death, love, murder, and dreams coming true. In other words, the usual. On Netflix from May 28.   If you missed out on Survivor: Winners at War, now is your time to binge the reality series on Showmax. Twenty winners of Survivor return to compete against each other for a prize of $2 million. Alliances, gruelling challenges and the Edge of Extinction … The most epic season yet! Now showing on Showmax.   Saving Our Marriage, presented by Anchor Psychologist, Ilze Alberts and Marriage Coach, Paul Nyamuda provides relationship coaching to couples who are facing issues and need an intervention. The professional coaches will provide them with much-needed therapy, whilst giving them a new outlook on their marriages and views on one another. Airs on SABC3 on Wednesdays at 7:30pm. View trailer here: https://www.facebook.com/watch/?v=436251764065529